"default":true,"description":"Documentation & tutorials"},{"id":3105906374,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwzMTA1OTA2Mzc0","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/labels/module:forecasting","name":"module:forecasting","color":"35FCCE","default":false,"description":""}],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":2,"created_at":"2021-09-27T16:04:22Z","updated_at":"2021-09-27T16:30:50Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"> #### Describe the issue linked to the documentation\r\n\r\nThe ForecastGorizon interface allows seperated steps forecasting (like `fh=[-10, -5, 3]`) but the forecaster (like pmdarima) is performing in this case a forecast from -10 to 3. The documentation says:\r\n\r\n```\r\nX: pd.DataFrame, optional (default=None)\r\nExogeneous data\r\n```\r\nBut it doesn't explain that X should have all exogenous values from relative step -10 to 3 (because that's what pmdarima is expecting).\r\n","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/1462/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/1462/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}